<subSubSection id="BAF265724F3CFF900731F9D7FB3E510F" pageId="17" pageNumber="1285" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3CFF900731F9D7FB3E510F" blockId="17.[809,1425,1602,1900]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1285">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3CFF900731F9D7FC3E5033" box="[809,928,1602,1623]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1285">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
S3/4 deep, V-shaped, completely traversing sternum (or deep at margins, faint in the middle); outer margins of S4 raised and thickened; third maxilliped ischium lacking vertical suture (or if present, faint); anterolateral margin of carapace posterior to epibranchial tooth either smooth or granulated, but lacking teeth; G1 TA short (TA length 0.25 × SA length), slim, either not widened in midsection (or dorsal fold slightly higher than ventral fold), tapering evenly to pointed tip (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3CFF900039F8C3FB0F510F" box="[1057,1169,1878,1900]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="15.[145,224,1409,1431]" captionTargetBox="[145,1425,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-190@15.[145,1425,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 5. Gonopods 1 and 2 of one genus in Maritimonautini and three genera in Potamonautini. A–C, Maritimonautes obesus; D–F, Arcopotamonautes suprasulcatus; G–I, Lirrangopotamonautes dybowskii; J–L, Platythelphusa armata. Scale bar: A, B, G–L = 2.0 mm, C, F = 1.8 mm; D, E = 5.0 mm; L = 6.7 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461489/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1285">Fig. 5A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
